<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>react on Gabriel Lazcano</title><link>https://gabriellazcano.com/tags/react/</link><description>Recent content in react on Gabriel Lazcano</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><copyright>Â© 2021 Gabriel Lazcano</copyright><lastBuildDate>Wed, 10 Aug 2022 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://gabriellazcano.com/tags/react/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>React Hooks gives you superpowers</title><link>https://gabriellazcano.com/blog/react-hooks-give-you-superpowers/</link><pubDate>Wed, 10 Aug 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gabriellazcano.com/blog/react-hooks-give-you-superpowers/</guid><description>&lt;p>React Hooks launched a long time ago, but it has now become a core part of React. It is a new way to write components that is much more powerful than the previous version.&lt;/p>
